name: Venusaur V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Solar Typhoon.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Eldegoss V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: You may shuffle this Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your deck.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Victini
flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Incineroar V
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Carvanha
flavorText: With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It's very sensitive to the scent of blood.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Wailord V
Attack1Text: Attach up to 3 Water Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 120 damage for each heads.

name: Drednaw V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Drednaw VMAX
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Gardevoir V
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon was healed during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Gardevoir VMAX
Attack1Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Hatenna
flavorText: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: Hattrem
flavorText: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

name: Hatterene
flavorText: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Galarian Cursola V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokémon, put 3 damage counters on that Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Alcremie V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Alcremie VMAX
Attack1Text: For each of your Benched Pokémon, search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to that Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard any amount of Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Machamp
flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Fighting Pokémon in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Lucario V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Beatdown Smash.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fighting Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Grapploct V
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

name: Arbok
flavorText: After stunning its opponents with the pattern on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its body and waits for them to stop moving.

name: Galarian Zigzagoon
flavorText: Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokémon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Galarian Linoone
flavorText: It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokémon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Obstagoon
flavorText: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may have your opponent discard cards from their hand until they have 4 cards in their hand.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Absol
flavorText: The elderly call it the disaster Pokémon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: As halfhearted as this Pokémon's kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr's concrete pillars.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If you played Piers from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Confused, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Malamar
flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Duraludon V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Swablu
flavorText: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

name: Altaria
flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V and Pokémon-GX.

Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

Attack2Text: If this Pokémon was healed during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage.

Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.
